resources.string: Logical reasoning tests (also known as critical reasoning tests) are designed to assess a candidate\'s ability at skills such as how to interpret patterns, number sequences or the relationships between shapes.

A person with spatial aptitude has the ability to understand three dimensional shapes. The ability to imagine the movement and interaction of objects and shapes is a characteristic of spatial aptitude.
Numerical aptitude refers to an individual\'s capacity to quickly perform mathematical operations.
Verbal Aptitude is the ability to use the written language and to understand concepts presented through words.
Rapid Evaluation Ability is the ability of an individual to access the situation quickly.
